Heat oil in medium saucepan over medium heat and saute onion until softened, about 5 minutes. Add cayenne, coriander, garlic, ginger, and turmeric and stir 3 to 4 minutes. Mix in tomato and cook until soft, about 5 minutes. Add 1 cup dillweed, chickpeas, water, and salt and simmer 5 minutes. Sprinkle with the remaining 1/2 cup dillweed.